narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a typical Yale math course, you won't learn in class and you'll have to do it all yourself.
Miserable class if your professor/grad student can't teach. It's also a lot of material.

I took this class to fulfill requirements for a bio major and premed. If at all possible, avoid this class. It is very poorly taught (mostly TAs) and the difficulty level of the tests is unreasonable considering the level of material covered in class. If you have to take it for a requirement, prepare to do a lot of work on your own.
